                <h1>Exploring the Meaning of Quinn: Origin & Significance</h1>
                <p>Quinn is a name of Irish origin, meaning "wisdom" or "intelligence." Traditionally used as a surname, it has evolved into a popular given name for both boys and girls. Known for its strong, vibrant sound, Quinn signifies a spirited and clever personality, often associated with leadership and creativity in those who bear the name.</p>
